SIMPLE: inexcusable
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inexcusable
<hw>In`ex*cus"a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>inexcusabilis</ets>: cf. F. <ets>inexcusable</ets>. See
<er>Excuse</er>.]</ety> <def>Not excusable; not admitting excuse or
justification; <as>as, <ex>inexcusable</ex> folly</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Therefore thou art <qex>inexcusable</qex>, O man, whosoever thou
art that judgest; for wherein thou judgest another, thou condemnest
thyself; for thou that judgest doest the same things.</q> <rj><qau>Rom.
ii. 1.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inexcusableness</ent>⟦br⟧
